# my-nestjs-api

> AGENTS.md: instructions for AI coding agents working on this project.
> Human contributors: see README.md.

## Stack

- Node.js
- NestJS 10.3.0

## Commands

- `npm run start`: `nest start`
- `npm run dev`: `nest start --watch`
- `npm run build`: `nest build`
- `npm run test`: `jest`

## Conventions

- ES modules (`"type": "module"`) with explicit `.js` extensions on imports.
- Use native fetch where available. Reserve axios for interceptor-heavy flows.
- One feature per module: controller + service + DTOs colocated under the same directory.
- Validate bodies with `class-validator` DTOs and a global `ValidationPipe`.
- Inject dependencies through the constructor. Prefer interface tokens for swappable implementations.

## What to avoid

- Mixing CommonJS and ESM in the same package.
- Business logic in controllers. Delegate to services; controllers only wire HTTP to service calls.

---

*Generated by [ContextEngine](https://github.com/strifero/ContextEngine). Re-run to refresh.*

